    <svcsubsec id="s26510.3">
        <title>Description of Engine Electrical Components - Chassis Mounted</title>
        <svcproc id="s26510.3.1" graphiccount="1">
            <title>ECM (Electronic Control Module)</title>
            <figure id="e3001137" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ09/J09013.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>ECM and IDM Modules</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">IDM</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">ECM</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The ECM monitors and controls engine performance to ensure maximum performance and adherence to
                emissions standards. The ECM is mounted to the large support bracket located behind the cab. The dust
                cover must be removed to access the ECM.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
